The paper discusses the performance evaluation of user-centric joint transmission in ultra-dense networks, which involves the use of distributed radio access points and virtual cells. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer communication (cs.COM). However, given the focus on wireless communication and network optimization, we believe that cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, followed by cs.MM, cs.SY, and cs.COM.
